  "text": "The 3D Enveloping Contact model was based on the work done by Schmeitz [CITATION_1] . Schmeitz proposed a cam model to emulate the enveloping behaviour of the tyre. The model comprises a number of cams 8 that are positioned in such a way that they correspond to the outside of the contact patch, as shown in Fig. 3 . Due to the shape of the cams this model is also referred to as the \"tandem-egg\" model.",
